      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:196:9",
      "text": [
        " لَا يَزَالُ الْهَمُّ وَ الْغَمُّ بِالْمُؤْمِنِ حَتَّى مَا يَدَعُ لَهُ مِنْ ذَنْبٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Ali Al Ahmasy, from a man, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The worries and the grief do not cease to be with the <span class=\"iTxt\">Momin</span> until there is nothing left for him, from a sin’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "9. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Ali al- Ahmasi from a man from abu Ja’far (a.s.) who has said the following: “Abu Ja’far (a.s.) has said, ‘A believer continues facing anxiety and sadness until no sin is left in him.’” "
        ]
      }
